<div class="component article-body-text    " data-test="article-body-text">
  
  

	

	
	

	
	



  
  
    <p>Over three weeks, we (Simon and Rebecca) swapped our irons for clothes steamers to see how effective they really were. We steamed shirts, dresses, trousers and bedding in various fabrics. We were looking for ease of use, tank capacity, heat-up time, cord length and useful extra features. Heres what we found, starting with our favourite...</p><hr /><h2 class="u-heading-size-large u-heading-style-normal"><a class="ck-anchor" id="best-clothes-steamers" name="best-clothes-steamers">Best clothes steamers</a></h2><p></p><h2 class="u-heading-size-medium u-heading-style-normal">1. Russell Hobbs Steam Genie 2-in-1 Garment Steamer</h2><p><a class="ck-custom-link" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Russell-Hobbs-28370-Clothes-Steamer/dp/B0B2DMM78J/ref&#61;asc_df_B0B2DMM78J/?tag&#61;telegraphaffiliate-21&amp;ascsubtag&#61;customid-21" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">39, Amazon</a></p><p><strong>Best overall, 9/10</strong></p><p><strong>We like: </strong>its extremely powerful</p><p><strong>We dont like: </strong>all the weight is at one end</p>
  
