    <ul><li>1100W power</li><li>180ml water tank</li><li>1.9m cord</li><li>1.08kg weight</li></ul><p>I generally find Beldray products outperform their price and are excellent options for anyone either foraying into the world of a new appliance, or perhaps looking for a cheaper option to match lesser use. (Their Titanium Smartflex made my review of the <a class="ck-custom-link" href="https://www.telegraph.co.uk/recommended/home/best-cordless-vacuums/">best cordless vacuums</a>). Beldrays clothes steamer is no different - a reliable workhorse for less than 25.</p><p>Thats not to say it compromises on quality, with a ceramic soleplate and a fabric attachment that looks luxe, a fast 30 second heat up time and a 180ml detachable water tank. It couldnt be easier to use and I particularly like the lock function, which emits continuous steam rather than using the trigger button. The ceramic soleplate is smooth over clothes and the 180ml water tank is plenty.</p><p>The cord is a little shorter than those I rate more highly so youll need to be nearer a plug. The body of the steamer also looks and feels quite plasticky, although it does curve pleasingly in hand and is lovely and lightweight. Considering its not the kind of appliance youll have on display, the cheap look isnt really a problem.</p>
  
</div>
