    <ul><li>1200W power</li><li>260ml water tank</li><li>1.9m cord</li><li>930g weight</li></ul><p>Amazons Beautural Steamer is not too dissimilar from the Beldray above, with the same lock function on the trigger button, removable water tank at the foot and 1.9m cord. The key differences are separate lint and soft brush attachments and a creaser, an attachment designed to steam trousers or remove particularly stubborn creases. Effectively, the creaser clamps the clothes to the steamer for particularly intense steaming.</p><p>My only criticism is the weight distribution - the large head holds the majority of the weight, so although this clothes steamer is actually lighter than the Beldray above, it feels heavier. As someone with weak wrists, I can imagine tiring during longer loads of washing. But for a budget option, thats me nitpicking.</p>
  
