<div class="articleBodyText section">




<div class="component article-body-text    " data-test="article-body-text">
  
  

	

	
	

	
	



  
  
    <ul><li>2200 Watts</li><li>3.3l water tank</li><li>7.5kg</li></ul><p><em>Reviewed by Rebecca Astill</em></p><p>To put the power of this steamer into context, I tested it in the office and had to ask security to switch the smoke alarm off, to avoid a full office evacuation. It uses 2200 Watts, which is almost double that of most other clothes steamers we tried, and five bars of pressure.</p><p>The Fridja F1500 is an upright clothes steamer, also known as a standing steamer, vertical steamer or freestanding steamer. To use them, you hang your clothes on the hanger at the top, fill up the water tank at the bottom and steam away. Upright steamers are expensive, but are a worthwhile investment for anyone who has a penchant for materials like linen, silk and cashmere which need de-wrinkling but are too delicate for an iron.</p><p>This Fridja F1500 is about the best youll find. Its the most powerful steamer I have tried, by far, but it is easy to use and doesnt spit. Where handheld steamers can struggle to remove deep creases, the five bars of pressure in this Fridja eradicated them within seconds. I find linen to be the stubbornest of materials, but this steamer didnt struggle at all, even with thicker trousers. It ironed out a crumpled shirt in just over a minute.</p><p>This steamer is a great option for anyone who hates ironing but has a high maintenance wardrobe. It takes all the fuss out of ironing and actually makes it almost, dare I say, fun?</p>
  
